{
  "feature": "Add Rate Limiting Middleware to API Routes",
  "description": "# Add Rate Limiting Middleware to API Routes\n\nImplement consistent rate limiting across all API routes using a middleware solution (e.g., Upstash Rate Limit or custom Redis-based limiter). Protect against abuse, bot sign-ups, and API overuse.\n\n## Rationale\nThe platform handles wallet top-ups, KYC data, and personal information — security is paramount. Without rate limiting, the platform is vulnerable to abuse, which could expose businesses and workers to fraud. This directly addresses technical debt identified in the codebase.\n\n## User Stories\n- As a business owner, I want the platform to be secure and protected from abuse so that my wallet balance and worker data are safe\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All public API routes have rate limiting configured (e.g., 100 req/min for reads, 20 req/min for writes)\n- [ ] Rate limit exceeded returns a 429 status with a Retry-After header\n- [ ] Rate limit configuration is environment-aware (different limits for dev/staging/prod)",
  "workflow_type": "feature",
  "workflow_rationale": "This is a multi-service feature that requires modifying 25 API route files to add rate limiting. The implementation can be parallelized by grouping routes by type.",
  "created_at": "2026-03-26T13:03:15.177Z",
  "updated_at": "2026-03-26T13:14:06.773Z",
  "status": "in_progress",
  "planStatus": "in_progress",
